<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1074" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.112H35/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Full mail report to-day re Heberlein, including his declaration, follows
                            by mail. He was released 10th instant; now in United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>